The paper deals with the use of row sampling for approximating matrix algorithms, which is a topic that falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of leverage scores and non-commutative Bernstein bounds also suggests that the paper may be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the focus on algorithms and computational complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS).
